Lindsay Jo Rimer was 13 when she went missing from Hebden Bridge in 1994 . 
  Her body was found in a canal five months later weighed down with a 20lb rock . 
  Her sister Kate Rimer has spoken of her family's struggle to find her killer 20 years after her death . 
  She described the struggle as a 'life sentence' for the family . 
  West Yorkshire Police have launched a new bid to find the teenager's killer . 
 